<br>
I did not address what was &quot;reasonable&quot; in my last post because I acknowledged that &quot;reasonable&quot; is subjective and tried to approach this issue from another view point. If you would like an example of what I thnk is unreasonable here it is.<br>
<br>
- I am a new player to EQ.<br>
- I make a Dwarven paladin.<br>
- I fight evil creature and do several cool quests turning in these bird claws, bone chips and orc shoulder pads. All in all having a good time.<br>
<br>
- Soon enough I am in unrest, battleing undead as paladins were meant to do. I am quickly approaching my 20th season as the creatures in unrest present a wide level of challenges.<br>
<br>
- I kill a carrion ghoul and loot its heart. I am told that it is part of a quest for a holy sword called Ghoulbane, which I will need for my epic. Being new I don't know what an Epic is so it is gleefully explained to me. Then the person says, &quot;so ya, your epic. You went to FP and killed that level 9 guy for your first part didnt you?&quot;<br>
<br>
- Of course not. Not one NPC in butcherblock gives any clue to the paladin NPC in FP. How could I have known? How could I have planned for this? This hardly seems fair but I shrug it off and struggle on.<br>
<br>
- So I go to FP and try to hire a group in the level range appropriate for this NPC. I soon realize that no one can understand me because I speak dwarf and everyone else here speaks human. What a great oppourtunity to learn human! <br>
<br>
- I try to learn human, I am having trouble because I only speak Dwarf so trying to explain that I want to learn human isnt easy. after &lt;&lt;insert time between 15 min and 1 week, as posted on this thread&gt;&gt; and becoming a master of miming &quot;I want to learn human&quot; someone finally clues in and agrees to teach me human.<br>
<br>
- ZOINKS! Languages are broken. No one can learn a language past skill 5 till verant gets it fixed, that is when they finally acknowledgd languages were broken in the first place which they wouldn't do. Now I have to try and find a group of dwarves to come help me do this, which really limits me since I can only solicit help form one race now. I can entice them with a 20 minute boat ride where they can do, er..nothing! Whee!<br>
<br>
- Good News! Verant acknowledges languages are broken and fixes them. I try to learn human, after &lt;&lt;insert time between 15 min and 1 week, as posted on this thread&gt;&gt; someone finally clues in and agrees to teach me human. I thank brell that its not 1 point per hour &lt;like Verant has posted on the FV info section&gt; or I would be level 30 or higher by the time I could belt out a coherant message.<br>
<br>
- I auction and auction for someone to help me with this NPC. I am having trouble because auction only works in city zones which is mostly populated by folks level 5 and under &lt;if there is anyone even in the zone on this server&gt; so I decide to move out to west commons/Nro where there are folks hunting that are in the proper level range to help with this NPC.<br>
<br>
- Auction doesnt work here,  no such thing as /ooc and shout has a limited range so I run around to the different camps of humans trying to get some help. After &lt;&lt;insert time between 15min and 1 week, as posted on this thread&gt;&gt; I find someone to help me.<br>
<br>
- Unfortunately, they want my bronze BP that I got in unrest because they know its for my Epic and know they have me by the beard. (You didnt think I was going to say balls did you? I am a paladin after all).<br>
<br>
- Success! They have aquired the piece I need for my Epic! I happily hand over my bronze BP and thank Brell for blessing me with this item!<br>
<br>
Thats pretty much what I find unreasonable. Especially for an item that doesnt have any stats, real worth and isn't ever farmed on any server period.<br>
